subSubSection.paragraph:
Adult females of the two species differ in the number of pale longitudinal lines (see above), in the absence (in 

A. margaritae


sp. nov.

) or presence (

A. busacki

) of dark reticulation on the middle of the dorsum, and in the presence (in 

A. margaritae


sp. nov.

) or absence (in 

A. busacki

) of yellowish colouration on the anterior part of the body (see also 
Table 2
).
